The whole country belonged to the Ro- mans as ager publicus, and was let to plebeian holders‚ and the government was administered by pmesecti sent from Rome. The communities‚ pagi, have certain local officers‚ mag-istri pagi. Inside the pagi there exist guilds or collegia, some ⁴of ingenui, others of libertini, others of slaves. The col· legia are named partly from their tutelary divinities, partly from their handi- craft. They seem to exist chiefly for religious purposes, but they stand in some organic relation to the pagus.
